3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Sparse regression codes have applications in network analysis and modeling, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper uses the second moment method, which is a popular technique in probability theory and algorithm analysis.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper mentions squared error distortion, which is commonly used in image and video compression, falling under the scope of this sub-category.
